  69

  72             msg = "'Line2D' object has no property 'blarg'"

  90         # once without an ax kwarg and once with an ax kwarg and the new sharex
  91         # behaviour does not remove the visibility of the latter axis (as ax is

  94         axes = df.plot(subplots=True, title="blah")

 100             self._check_visible(ax.get_xticklabels(minor=True), visible=False)

 108         _check_plot_works(df.plot, title="blah")
 109

 114         # unicode

 191     def test_color_and_style_arguments(self):
 192         df = DataFrame({"x": [1, 2], "y": [3, 4]})
 193         # passing both 'color' and 'style' arguments should be allowed
 194         # if there is no color symbol in the style strings:
 195         ax = df.plot(color=["red", "black"], style=["-", "--"])
 196         # check that the linestyles are correctly set:
 197         linestyle = [line.get_linestyle() for line in ax.lines]
 198         assert linestyle == ["-", "--"]
 199         # check that the colors are correctly set:
 200         color = [line.get_color() for line in ax.lines]
 201         assert color == ["red", "black"]
 202         # passing both 'color' and 'style' arguments should not be allowed
 203         # if there is a color symbol in the style strings:
 204         with pytest.raises(ValueError):
 205             df.plot(color=["red", "black"], style=["k-", "r--"])

 230         self._check_data(df.plot(x=0, y=1), df.set_index("A")["B"].plot())
 231         self._check_data(df.plot(x=0), df.set_index("A").plot())
 232         self._check_data(df.plot(y=0), df.B.plot())

 240         self._check_data(df.plot(x=1), df.set_index(1).plot())
 241         self._check_data(df.plot(y=1), df[1].plot())

 255     def test_logscales(self, input_log, expected_log):
 256         df = DataFrame({"a": np.arange(100)}, index=np.arange(100))

 258         ax = df.plot(logy=input_log)

 280     @pytest.mark.slow
 281     def test_xcompat(self):
 282         import pandas as pd
 283 
 284         df = self.tdf
 285         ax = df.plot(x_compat=True)
 286         lines = ax.get_lines()
 287         assert not isinstance(lines[0].get_xdata(), PeriodIndex)
 288 
 289         tm.close()
 290         pd.plotting.plot_params["xaxis.compat"] = True
 291         ax = df.plot()
 292         lines = ax.get_lines()
 293         assert not isinstance(lines[0].get_xdata(), PeriodIndex)
 294 
 295         tm.close()
 296         pd.plotting.plot_params["x_compat"] = False
 297 
 298         ax = df.plot()
 299         lines = ax.get_lines()
 300         assert not isinstance(lines[0].get_xdata(), PeriodIndex)
 301         assert isinstance(PeriodIndex(lines[0].get_xdata()), PeriodIndex)
 302 
 303         tm.close()
 304         # useful if you're plotting a bunch together
 305         with pd.plotting.plot_params.use("x_compat", True):
 306             ax = df.plot()
 307             lines = ax.get_lines()
 308             assert not isinstance(lines[0].get_xdata(), PeriodIndex)
 309 
 310         tm.close()
 311         ax = df.plot()
 312         lines = ax.get_lines()
 313         assert not isinstance(lines[0].get_xdata(), PeriodIndex)
 314         assert isinstance(PeriodIndex(lines[0].get_xdata()), PeriodIndex)

 329     def test_unsorted_index(self):
 330         df = DataFrame(
 331             {"y": np.arange(100)}, index=np.arange(99, -1, -1), dtype=np.int64
 332         )
 333         ax = df.plot()
 334         lines = ax.get_lines()[0]
 335         rs = lines.get_xydata()
 336         rs = Series(rs[:, 1], rs[:, 0], dtype=np.int64, name="y")
 337         tm.assert_series_equal(rs, df.y, check_index_type=False)
 338         tm.close()
 339 
 340         df.index = pd.Index(np.arange(99, -1, -1), dtype=np.float64)
 341         ax = df.plot()
 342         lines = ax.get_lines()[0]
 343         rs = lines.get_xydata()
 344         rs = Series(rs[:, 1], rs[:, 0], dtype=np.int64, name="y")
 345         tm.assert_series_equal(rs, df.y)

 347     def test_unsorted_index_lims(self):
 348         df = DataFrame({"y": [0.0, 1.0, 2.0, 3.0]}, index=[1.0, 0.0, 3.0, 2.0])
 349         ax = df.plot()
 350         xmin, xmax = ax.get_xlim()
 351         lines = ax.get_lines()
 352         assert xmin <= np.nanmin(lines[0].get_data()[0])
 353         assert xmax >= np.nanmax(lines[0].get_data()[0])
 354 
 355         df = DataFrame(
 356             {"y": [0.0, 1.0, np.nan, 3.0, 4.0, 5.0, 6.0]},
 357             index=[1.0, 0.0, 3.0, 2.0, np.nan, 3.0, 2.0],
 358         )
 359         ax = df.plot()
 360         xmin, xmax = ax.get_xlim()
 361         lines = ax.get_lines()
 362         assert xmin <= np.nanmin(lines[0].get_data()[0])
 363         assert xmax >= np.nanmax(lines[0].get_data()[0])
 364 
 365         df = DataFrame({"y": [0.0, 1.0, 2.0, 3.0], "z": [91.0, 90.0, 93.0, 92.0]})
 366         ax = df.plot(x="z", y="y")
 367         xmin, xmax = ax.get_xlim()
 368         lines = ax.get_lines()
 369         assert xmin <= np.nanmin(lines[0].get_data()[0])
 370         assert xmax >= np.nanmax(lines[0].get_data()[0])

 372     @pytest.mark.slow
 373     def test_subplots(self):
 374         df = DataFrame(np.random.rand(10, 3), index=list(string.ascii_letters[:10]))
 375 
 376         for kind in ["bar", "barh", "line", "area"]:
 377             axes = df.plot(kind=kind, subplots=True, sharex=True, legend=True)
 378             self._check_axes_shape(axes, axes_num=3, layout=(3, 1))
 379             assert axes.shape == (3,)
 380 
 381             for ax, column in zip(axes, df.columns):
 382                 self._check_legend_labels(ax, labels=[pprint_thing(column)])
 383 
 384             for ax in axes[:-2]:
 385                 self._check_visible(ax.xaxis)  # xaxis must be visible for grid
 386                 self._check_visible(ax.get_xticklabels(), visible=False)
 387                 if not (kind == "bar" and self.mpl_ge_3_1_0):
 388                     # change https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/issues/26714
 389                     self._check_visible(ax.get_xticklabels(minor=True), visible=False)
 390                 self._check_visible(ax.xaxis.get_label(), visible=False)
 391                 self._check_visible(ax.get_yticklabels())
 392 
 393             self._check_visible(axes[-1].xaxis)
 394             self._check_visible(axes[-1].get_xticklabels())
 395             self._check_visible(axes[-1].get_xticklabels(minor=True))
 396             self._check_visible(axes[-1].xaxis.get_label())
 397             self._check_visible(axes[-1].get_yticklabels())
 398 
 399             axes = df.plot(kind=kind, subplots=True, sharex=False)
 400             for ax in axes:
 401                 self._check_visible(ax.xaxis)
 402                 self._check_visible(ax.get_xticklabels())
 403                 self._check_visible(ax.get_xticklabels(minor=True))
 404                 self._check_visible(ax.xaxis.get_label())
 405                 self._check_visible(ax.get_yticklabels())
 406 
 407             axes = df.plot(kind=kind, subplots=True, legend=False)
 408             for ax in axes:
 409                 assert ax.get_legend() is None

 417             {

 433         self._assert_ytickslabels_visibility(axes, expected)

 436         axes = df.groupby("c").boxplot(sharey=False)
 437         expected = [True, True, True, True]
 438         self._assert_ytickslabels_visibility(axes, expected)

 549     @pytest.mark.xfail(reason="not support for period, categorical, datetime_mixed_tz")
 550     def test_subplots_timeseries_y_axis_not_supported(self):
 551         """
 552         This test will fail for:
 553             period:
 554                 since period isn't yet implemented in ``select_dtypes``
 555                 and because it will need a custom value converter +
 556                 tick formatter (as was done for x-axis plots)
 557 
 558             categorical:
 559                  because it will need a custom value converter +
 560                  tick formatter (also doesn't work for x-axis, as of now)
 561 
 562             datetime_mixed_tz:
 563                 because of the way how pandas handles ``Series`` of
 564                 ``datetime`` objects with different timezone,
 565                 generally converting ``datetime`` objects in a tz-aware
 566                 form could help with this problem
 567         """
 568         data = {
 569             "numeric": np.array([1, 2, 5]),
 570             "period": [
 571                 pd.Period("2017-08-01 00:00:00", freq="H"),
 572                 pd.Period("2017-08-01 02:00", freq="H"),
 573                 pd.Period("2017-08-02 00:00:00", freq="H"),
 574             ],
 575             "categorical": pd.Categorical(
 576                 ["c", "b", "a"], categories=["a", "b", "c"], ordered=False
 577             ),
 578             "datetime_mixed_tz": [
 579                 pd.to_datetime("2017-08-01 00:00:00", utc=True),
 580                 pd.to_datetime("2017-08-01 02:00:00"),
 581                 pd.to_datetime("2017-08-02 00:00:00"),
 582             ],
 583         }
 584         testdata = pd.DataFrame(data)
 585         ax_period = testdata.plot(x="numeric", y="period")
 586         assert (
 587             ax_period.get_lines()[0].get_data()[1] == testdata["period"].values
 588         ).all()
 589         ax_categorical = testdata.plot(x="numeric", y="categorical")
 590         assert (
 591             ax_categorical.get_lines()[0].get_data()[1]
 592             == testdata["categorical"].values
 593         ).all()
 594         ax_datetime_mixed_tz = testdata.plot(x="numeric", y="datetime_mixed_tz")
 595         assert (
 596             ax_datetime_mixed_tz.get_lines()[0].get_data()[1]
 597             == testdata["datetime_mixed_tz"].values
 598         ).all()

1393     def _check_bar_alignment(
1394         self,
1395         df,
1396         kind="bar",
1397         stacked=False,
1398         subplots=False,
1399         align="center",
1400         width=0.5,
1401         position=0.5,
1402     ):
1403 
1404         axes = df.plot(
1405             kind=kind,
1406             stacked=stacked,
1407             subplots=subplots,
1408             align=align,
1409             width=width,
1410             position=position,
1411             grid=True,
1412         )
1413 
1414         axes = self._flatten_visible(axes)
1415 
1416         for ax in axes:
1417             if kind == "bar":
1418                 axis = ax.xaxis
1419                 ax_min, ax_max = ax.get_xlim()
1420                 min_edge = min(p.get_x() for p in ax.patches)
1421                 max_edge = max(p.get_x() + p.get_width() for p in ax.patches)
1422             elif kind == "barh":
1423                 axis = ax.yaxis
1424                 ax_min, ax_max = ax.get_ylim()
1425                 min_edge = min(p.get_y() for p in ax.patches)
1426                 max_edge = max(p.get_y() + p.get_height() for p in ax.patches)
1427             else:
1428                 raise ValueError
1429 
1430             # GH 7498
1431             # compare margins between lim and bar edges
1432             tm.assert_almost_equal(ax_min, min_edge - 0.25)
1433             tm.assert_almost_equal(ax_max, max_edge + 0.25)
1434 
1435             p = ax.patches[0]
1436             if kind == "bar" and (stacked is True or subplots is True):
1437                 edge = p.get_x()
1438                 center = edge + p.get_width() * position
1439             elif kind == "bar" and stacked is False:
1440                 center = p.get_x() + p.get_width() * len(df.columns) * position
1441                 edge = p.get_x()
1442             elif kind == "barh" and (stacked is True or subplots is True):
1443                 center = p.get_y() + p.get_height() * position
1444                 edge = p.get_y()
1445             elif kind == "barh" and stacked is False:
1446                 center = p.get_y() + p.get_height() * len(df.columns) * position
1447                 edge = p.get_y()
1448             else:
1449                 raise ValueError
1450 
1451             # Check the ticks locates on integer
1452             assert (axis.get_ticklocs() == np.arange(len(df))).all()
1453 
1454             if align == "center":
1455                 # Check whether the bar locates on center
1456                 tm.assert_almost_equal(axis.get_ticklocs()[0], center)
1457             elif align == "edge":
1458                 # Check whether the bar's edge starts from the tick
1459                 tm.assert_almost_equal(axis.get_ticklocs()[0], edge)
1460             else:
1461                 raise ValueError
1462 
1463         return axes

1889     @pytest.mark.slow
1890     def test_df_legend_labels(self):
1891         kinds = ["line", "bar", "barh", "kde", "area", "hist"]
1892         df = DataFrame(rand(3, 3), columns=["a", "b", "c"])
1893         df2 = DataFrame(rand(3, 3), columns=["d", "e", "f"])
1894         df3 = DataFrame(rand(3, 3), columns=["g", "h", "i"])
1895         df4 = DataFrame(rand(3, 3), columns=["j", "k", "l"])
1896 
1897         for kind in kinds:
1898 
1899             ax = df.plot(kind=kind, legend=True)
1900             self._check_legend_labels(ax, labels=df.columns)
1901 
1902             ax = df2.plot(kind=kind, legend=False, ax=ax)
1903             self._check_legend_labels(ax, labels=df.columns)
1904 
1905             ax = df3.plot(kind=kind, legend=True, ax=ax)
1906             self._check_legend_labels(ax, labels=df.columns.union(df3.columns))
1907 
1908             ax = df4.plot(kind=kind, legend="reverse", ax=ax)
1909             expected = list(df.columns.union(df3.columns)) + list(reversed(df4.columns))
1910             self._check_legend_labels(ax, labels=expected)
1911 
1912         # Secondary Y
1913         ax = df.plot(legend=True, secondary_y="b")
1914         self._check_legend_labels(ax, labels=["a", "b (right)", "c"])
1915         ax = df2.plot(legend=False, ax=ax)
1916         self._check_legend_labels(ax, labels=["a", "b (right)", "c"])
1917         ax = df3.plot(kind="bar", legend=True, secondary_y="h", ax=ax)
1918         self._check_legend_labels(
1919             ax, labels=["a", "b (right)", "c", "g", "h (right)", "i"]
1920         )
1921 
1922         # Time Series
1923         ind = date_range("1/1/2014", periods=3)

2841     @pytest.mark.slow
2842     def test_sharex_and_ax(self):
2843         # https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/issues/9737 using gridspec,
2844         # the axis in fig.get_axis() are sorted differently than pandas
2845         # expected them, so make sure that only the right ones are removed
2846         import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
2847 
2848         plt.close("all")
2849         gs, axes = _generate_4_axes_via_gridspec()
2850 
2851         df = DataFrame(
2852             {
2853                 "a": [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6],
2854                 "b": [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6],
2855                 "c": [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6],
2856                 "d": [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6],
2857             }
2858         )
2859 
2860         def _check(axes):
2861             for ax in axes:
2862                 assert len(ax.lines) == 1
2863                 self._check_visible(ax.get_yticklabels(), visible=True)
2864             for ax in [axes[0], axes[2]]:
2865                 self._check_visible(ax.get_xticklabels(), visible=False)
2866                 self._check_visible(ax.get_xticklabels(minor=True), visible=False)
2867             for ax in [axes[1], axes[3]]:
2868                 self._check_visible(ax.get_xticklabels(), visible=True)
2869                 self._check_visible(ax.get_xticklabels(minor=True), visible=True)
2870 
2871         for ax in axes:
2872             df.plot(x="a", y="b", title="title", ax=ax, sharex=True)
2873         gs.tight_layout(plt.gcf())
2874         _check(axes)
2875         tm.close()
2876 
2877         gs, axes = _generate_4_axes_via_gridspec()
2878         with tm.assert_produces_warning(UserWarning):
2879             axes = df.plot(subplots=True, ax=axes, sharex=True)
2880         _check(axes)
2881         tm.close()
2882 
2883         gs, axes = _generate_4_axes_via_gridspec()
2884         # without sharex, no labels should be touched!
2885         for ax in axes:
2886             df.plot(x="a", y="b", title="title", ax=ax)
2887 
2888         gs.tight_layout(plt.gcf())
2889         for ax in axes:
2890             assert len(ax.lines) == 1
2891             self._check_visible(ax.get_yticklabels(), visible=True)
2892             self._check_visible(ax.get_xticklabels(), visible=True)
2893             self._check_visible(ax.get_xticklabels(minor=True), visible=True)

3365 def _generate_4_axes_via_gridspec():
3366     import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
3367     import matplotlib as mpl
3368     import matplotlib.gridspec  # noqa
3369 
3370     gs = mpl.gridspec.GridSpec(2, 2)
3371     ax_tl = plt.subplot(gs[0, 0])
3372     ax_ll = plt.subplot(gs[1, 0])
3373     ax_tr = plt.subplot(gs[0, 1])
3374     ax_lr = plt.subplot(gs[1, 1])
3375 
3376     return gs, [ax_tl, ax_ll, ax_tr, ax_l
